<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Show veterans will be joined by some brand new faces when Made In Chelsea  returns with a summer to remember from 28th September.</p>

<p>After a brief visit to the legendary SW3 location earlier this year due - the result of the COVID-19 crisis - the award-winning reality show is back, and a brand new trailer suggests it will be better than ever. </p>

<p>The cast will be back on the Kings Road, but exclusive new footage suggests a trip to the countryside will also be on the cards when they leave London for trips to two luxurious country manors.  </p>

<p>Coming soon: Show veterans will be joined by some brand-new faces when Made In Chelsea returns with a summer to remember from 28th September</p>

<p>Questions urgently need answering during the new series, namely will Olivia Bentley be in with a chance of a summer fling as some new faces join the group on her country getaway with close friend Tiffany Watson? </p>

<p>There may well be plenty of opportunity, with Harvey Armstrong, Emily Blackwell, Verity Bowditch, Freddie Browne, Maeva D’Ascanio, Sam Holmes, Amelia Mist, Tristan Phipps and James Taylor also along for what promises to be an eventful ride. </p>

<p>However the close proximity could lead to heated face-offs as Verity and Tristan meet for the first time since ending their relationship over the phone. </p>

<p>Stunning: The cast will be back on the Kings Road, but exclusive new footage suggests a trip to the countryside will also be on the cards when they leave London for trips to two luxurious country manors</p>

<p>Romance: Questions urgently need answering during the new series, namely will Olivia Bentley be in with a chance of a summer fling as some new faces join the group</p>

<p>The country residents will be accompanied by some new faces in the form of Amelia’s close friend, Paris Smith, and personal trainer and former Love Island star Charlie Frederick, who will endeavour to keep the holidaying stars fit.   </p>

<p>Back in London there appears to be further conflict in store for Sam Thomson and Zara McDermott after it emerged that Sam told ex Tiff that his relationship with the former Love Island star is the best thing to ever happen to him. </p>

<p>However tempers appear to reach boiling point when even more revelations come to light, but how will Zara react?</p>

<p>Old friend: Tiffany Watson will join Liv and the gang on their lavish country getaway </p>

<p>Getting involved: The new faces will include personal trainer and former Love Island star Charlie Frederick, who will endeavour to keep the holidaying stars fit</p>

<p>Meanwhile Ollie Locke and his fiancé Gareth are concerned about what to do for their winter wedding after their original plans were disrupted by the global health crisis, giving them a mountain to climb to reach their winter deadline. </p>

<p>New faces expected to feature in Chelsea include model Will Higginson and Reza’s girlfriend, Ruby Adler. </p>

<p>Made in Chelsea returns to E4 from the 28th September at 9pm. Catch up on All 4.  </p>

<p>Awkward: Back in London there appears to be further conflict in store for Sam Thomson and Zara McDermott</p>
